app.note:
DCS emends - dāsas tair iha.
notes: The author of the record thought of the dual number probably because Bhōyila and Mahīdāsa were residents of the same place while Kshemāka was the inhabitant of a different locality.. Another possibility would be to emend - kṣemāka-gulmagandhikāvāstavyabhoyila-tatraivavāstavya-mahīdāsair. But comparison with lists of witness containing the expression atraivavāstavya in the plate of Vainyagupta of 184 GE (
) suggests the emendations - kṣemāka ḥ gulmagandhikā-vāstavya-bhoyila s tatraiva-vāstavya-mahīdā saś ca Iha- (or ... dā saś ceha-).

